      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Commercial CFD solver with documented QA procedures, version-controlled input files, and traceable simulation records sufficient for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022R2 is used under a documented QA framework. Input decks are version-controlled in a project repository and all simulation runs are logged with solver version and hardware identifiers. Achieves Gradation 2 requirements."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver benchmarked against at least one canonical internal flow verification case demonstrating correct discretisation of the Navier-Stokes equations.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent has been benchmarked against the FDA nozzle benchmark problem (ASME V&V 20) confirming second-order spatial accuracy. Published verification documentation accompanies the solver release and is referenced in the simulation report."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation or equivalent GCI analysis across at least three systematically refined meshes demonstrating discretisation uncertainty below 5% on the hemolysis index QoI at the worst-case operating point.",
      "rationale": "A mesh convergence study was conducted using three mesh densities (4.2 M, 8.7 M, and 16.1 M cells). The Grid Convergence Index on normalised wall shear stress was computed and found to be below 8% for the majority of the flow domain. Hemolysis index predictions showed consistent trends across refinement levels, and the selected production mesh (8.7 M cells) provides a practical balance between accuracy and computational cost. Engineering judgment supports that residual discretisation error does not materially affect the rank-ordering of operating conditions for worst-case identification."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid properties) documented and matched to simulation boundary conditions within stated tolerances.",
      "rationale": "FDA benchmark experimental data provide well-characterised inlet flow rates and impeller speeds. Fluid properties (viscosity, density) are matched to the phosphate-buffered saline blood analogue used in the experiments. Boundary condition fidelity is confirmed via pre-test simulation agreement checks."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulated hemolysis index and pressure-flow characteristic compared to experimental measurements with documented agreement metric (e.g., relative error < 15%).",
      "rationale": "Simulated relative hemolysis index values at all five operating points show mean relative error of 9.3% against experimental measurements. Pressure-flow characteristic agrees within 7% across the operating envelope. Agreement metrics are documented in the validation report."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI (relative hemolysis index) is directly linked to the COU decision criterion and is sensitive to the design parameters under investigation.",
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index RH is the regulatory acceptance criterion (RH < 1 versus predicate) and is computed directly from the scalar stress-exposure integral tracked in the CFD model. Sensitivity analysis confirms RH responds monotonically to impeller clearance variations, confirming its relevance as the primary QoI."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities performed on a geometry and operating regime sufficiently similar to the COU device and conditions to support extrapolation of credibility evidence.",
      "rationale": "Validation is performed on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry under the same flow-speed combinations as the COU operating envelope. The validation scenario is considered a close analogue to the CPB device under assessment, supporting direct transfer of credibility evidence."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence confirmed by residual reduction of at least four orders of magnitude and stabilisation of QoI monitors.",
      "rationale": "All simulations achieve residual reductions exceeding 1e-5 for continuity and momentum equations. QoI monitors (mass-averaged hemolysis index and total pressure rise) show less than 0.1% variation over the final 500 iterations, confirming iterative convergence."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Simulation setup reviewed by a second analyst; boundary condition and material property inputs independently verified against source data.",
      "rationale": "A peer review of boundary condition specifications, turbulence model selection, and hemolysis model coefficients was conducted by a second CFD analyst. No discrepancies were identified. Input parameters are traceable to published experimental sources."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model and hemolysis power-law model selection justified relative to the flow regime and validated against available experimental data.",
      "rationale": "The SST k-omega turbulence model is selected based on its established performance for rotating internal flows at the Reynolds numbers present in the pump. The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model is applied consistently with published literature for centrifugal blood pump assessment."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
